parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: To have in full, be far, it is enough. From apo and echo; to have out, i.e. Receive in full; to keep away, i.e. Be distant.
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.

parse: Verb - Perfect Indicative Middle or Passive - 1st Person Singular
str2: From pleres; to make replete, i.e. to cram, level up, or to furnish, satisfy, execute, finish, verify, etc.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: From perissos; to superabound, be in excess, be superfluous; also to cause to superabound or excel.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Middle - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To take, receive, accept, welcome. Middle voice of a primary verb; to receive.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Gen: from; dat: beside, in the presence of; acc: alongside of.
From epi and Aphrodite; Epaphroditus, a Christian.
A sweet smell, fragrance. From a compound of eu and a derivative of ozo; good-scentedness, i.e. Fragrance.
A smell, odor, savor. From ozo; fragrance.
Acceptable, accepted. From dechomai; approved; propitious.
Abstr. and concr: sacrifice; a sacrifice, offering. From thuo; sacrifice.
Acceptable, well-pleasing (especially to God), grateful. From eu and arestos; fully agreeable.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
